      <section eId="sec_1166">
        <num>1166</num>
        <heading>Required position for turning at alley, driveway, private road or onto property off the roadway</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_1166__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Right turns. The approach for a right turn shall be made as close\nas practicable to the right-hand curb or edge of the roadway.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_1166__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Left turns from two-way roadways. The approach for a left turn\nfrom a two-way roadway shall be made in that portion of the right half\nof the roadway nearest the center thereof.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_1166__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Left turns from other than two-way roadways. The approach for a\nleft turn from a roadway on which traffic is restricted to one direction\nshall be made in the extreme left-hand lane lawfully available to\ntraffic.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
